DateTime ValueType Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph><Run FontWeight="Bold">DateTime ValueType Demo</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph>A chart can automatically compute an appropriate DateTime range based on the set ValueType. The DateTime range specifying the range can be done by setting AutoSetRange to false and then manually specifying the DateTimeInterval for the chart axis.

</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
<Image Source="Images\Axis DateTime ValueType Demo.png" Width="750" Height="600" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>DateTimeRange and DateTimeInterval of the chart axis can be auto-set or customized.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Checkbox <Bold>"ISAutoSetRange"</Bold>helps to set the IsAutoSetRange property for the Chart Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"Range"</Bold> helps to set the custom ranges. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The text box <Bold>"Interval"</Bold> helps to set the interval of Primary Axis.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
 
</List>
</FlowDocument>